1	/**
2	 * Integration tests for src/server/worktree/manager.ts
3	 *
4	 * Covers feat-worktree-mgr acceptance criteria:
5	 *   AC-1  createWorktree: branch name matches yoke/<slug>-<shortid>; branch_name
6	 *         and worktree_path written to the workflows row inside a transaction.
7	 *   AC-2  runBootstrap: commands run in declared order; non-zero exit triggers
8	 *         bootstrap_fail event and inserts pending_attention{kind=bootstrap_failed}.
9	 *   AC-3  bootstrap_failed never auto-cleans (enforced by state machine; tested
10	 *         here by confirming bootstrap_fail is the returned event type and that
11	 *         runBootstrap does NOT remove the worktree directory).
12	 *   AC-4  runTeardown: teardown.sh invoked if present; absence is not an error.
13	 *   AC-5  cleanup: refused (with warning) when branch has unpushed commits and
14	 *         no PR exists; proceeds when PR exists or no unpushed commits.
15	 *   AC-6  cleanup: ordered — kill pids → teardown → git worktree remove --force
16	 *         → branch retention.
17	 *
18	 * Also covers review criteria:
19	 *   RC-1  runBootstrap returns a BootstrapEvent (not void); this module does not
20	 *         call transition() — verified by absence of any import of transitions.ts.
21	 *   RC-2  _hasUnpushedCommits uses 'git log --not --remotes' (git remote state).
22	 *   RC-3  git worktree remove uses --force only after teardown has run.
23	 *   RC-4  Worktree path is absolute and validated to be under baseDir.
24	 *
25	 * Test infrastructure:
26	 *   - Each test gets a fresh temp directory with an initialised git repo and
27	 *     at least one commit (required for git worktree add).
28	 *   - A bare repository is used as a fake remote for retention-check tests.
29	 *   - A fresh SQLite database with migrations applied is provided per test.
30	 *   - The CheckPrFn seam is used to avoid requiring the gh CLI.
31	 */
